list.abstract: MUST是一款专注团队协作的移动软件。 通过群组的文档、任务、报表、上报等应用，实现团队组织的实名沟通、工作协作、任务追踪、资料归档、工作汇报等功能。此外，内置新闻客户端、考勤签到、快递管理、企业服务号等系统，也能解决企业管理等问题。 软件的2.07.66版本由于存在私自收集个人信息、超范围收集个人信息、过度索取权限、账号注销难等问题，中华人民共和国工业和信息化部发布《关于侵害用户权益行为的APP通报（2020年第三批）》，要求其在在2020年7月30日前完成整改落实工作。

yingyinNormal.en: We must act, Mr. President, and we must act now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们必须采取行动，总统先生，马上行动。

yingyinNormal.en: I must return to the line.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我必须回到前线去了。

yingyinNormal.en: The finding must be confirmed by other experiments.
yingyinNormal.zh: 该发现必须由其他实验确证。

yingyinNormal.en: It would ring hollow. The words must come from him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 会很空洞，那些话必须他说。

yingyinNormal.en: You must have your boarding pass. Ok. Fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 小姐，您必须要有登机牌。好的好的。

yingyinNormal.en: It is our technology. And it must be returned.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是我们的科技，必须要归还给我们。

yingyinNormal.en: Master! You can't leave me! You must believe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真人，你不能离我而去。你必须去相信。

yingyinNormal.en: Hatter, please. You must go back to your family.
yingyinNormal.zh: 疯帽子，拜托，你必须回到家人身边。

yingyinNormal.en: America is our enemy and must meet our demands.
yingyinNormal.zh: 美国是我们的敌人，必须满足我们的需求。

yingyinNormal.en: And I think Internet must find the missing part.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我认为，互联网必须找到那个缺失的部分。

yingyinNormal.en: No. You must be patient. But she's waiting for me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不行，你必须要有耐心。但她正在等我。

yingyinNormal.en: Violence cannot beget apathy. We must make our voices heard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 暴力不能导致冷漠。我们必须发声。

yingyinNormal.en: First, you must do some press-ups. Easy. One, two.
yingyinNormal.zh: 首先，你必须做一些俯卧撑。简单.一、二……

yingyinNormal.en: First, you must do some press-ups. Easy. One, two.
yingyinNormal.zh: 首先，你必须做一些俯卧撑.简单.一、二……

yingyinNormal.en: I must confess I don't understand you, President Siebert.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我必须承认我不懂你什么意思，希伯特校长。

yingyinNormal.en: But the rat! You must... It stole my documents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是那老鼠... 你必须... 那老鼠偷了我的餐厅。

yingyinNormal.en: We must hold everyone in government accountable to the law.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们必须让政府里的每一个人按章守法办事。

yingyinNormal.en: Survive. Bring peace between orcs and humans. You must.
yingyinNormal.zh: 活下去，为兽人与人类之间带来和平，你必须这样。

yingyinNormal.en: As your father, you must trust me. Patience. Patience.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作為你们的父亲， 你们必须相信我，耐心，再耐心。

yingyinNormal.en: Ok, but you must promise you'll stay awake. We promise.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，但是你们必须保证你们会保持清醒。我们保证。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 必须的；必须的条件；不可缺少的东西

examination_example.sentence: The challenge of coping with automation underlines the need for the U.S. to revive its fading business dynamism: Starting new companies <highlight>must</highlight> be made easier.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 应对自动化的挑战凸显出美国重振其日渐衰落的商业活力的必要性：必须让新公司的创办变得更容易。

examination_example.sentence: But under anti-bribery laws, proof <highlight>must</highlight> be made of concrete benefits, such as approval of a contract or regulation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但根据反贿赂法，证明必须带有具体的效益，如批准一份合同或一项规定。

examination_example.sentence: Elected leaders <highlight>must</highlight> be allowed to help supporters deal with bureaucratic problems without fear of prosecution of bribery.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当选的领导人必须被允许帮助支持者处理官僚问题，而不必担心被控受贿。

examination_example.sentence: Surely there <highlight>must</highlight> be some middle ground that balances zoos treatment of animals with their educational potential.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当然，必须要有一些中间立场来权衡动物园对待动物的方式和它们的教育潜力。

examination_example.sentence: Officials <highlight>must</highlight> not be allowed to play favorites in providing information or in arranging meetings simply because an individual or group provides a personal gift.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 官员不得因个人或团体提供私人礼物而在提供信息或安排会面时有所偏袒。

examination_example.sentence: His parents believe working steadily is a <highlight>must</highlight> for success.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的父母相信稳定的工作是成功的必要条件。

word_usage.usage: must作名词时，常用单数形式，如：His new novel is a must for all lovers of crime fiction. 他的新小说是所有犯罪小说爱好者的必备品。

word_usage.usage:
must表必然（表示根据逻辑推理必然要发生的事）：
All men must die.
人总有一死。

must表必须：
①用于肯定陈述句，表示说话人的主观意志，或必须做某事：
I must go now, or I’ll be late for class.
我得走了，否则上课要迟到了。
In the UK traffic must keep to the left.
在英国车辆必须靠左行驶。
② 在问句中用来征求听话人的意见，问某人是否必须做某事。回答时肯定回答用must, 否定回答用needn't 或don't have to：
Must I do it myself?
我必须自己动手做吗？ 
No, you needn't/don't have to. 
不，你不必。
③ 在否定句中表示说话人不许或禁止做某事：
You mustn't smoke in public places.
公共场所不准吸烟。

must表一定、必定（用于肯定句，表示推测）：
① 表示对现在的情况很有把握的推测：
You must be hungry and tired after such a long walk.
走了那么远的路，你一定又累又饿。
② 后跟进行时，表示对目前正在发生的事情的推测：
Right now they must be working on the farm.
现在他们一定在农场里干活。
③ 后跟完成时，表示对过去发生的事情的推测：
Peter has gone to work but his car is still here. He must have gone by bus.
彼得人去上班了，但车还在这儿。他一定是坐公共汽车去的。
④ 当must表推测时，不用于否定句或疑问句中，而用can't 或couldn't：
He can't have been to your home; he doesn't know your address.
他不可能去过你家，他不知道你的住址。

examination_example.sentence: First of all, you <highlight>must</highlight> wear shoes that cover your feet in the lab.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，在实验室里，你必须穿能盖住脚的鞋子。

examination_example.sentence: To read the message of a real code, you <highlight>must</highlight> have a code book.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要阅读真正代码的信息，你必须有一本代码手册。

examination_example.sentence: My 10-year-old noticed him and make a comment on how bad it <highlight>must</highlight> be to have to stand outside in the cold wind.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我10岁的孩子注意到了他，还说在寒风中站在外面一定很糟糕。

word_usage.usage:
must表示语气较肯定的推测，语气比may,might强烈。
如：I'm sorry,she’s not here. She must have left already.
对不起，她不在这里。她一定已经离开了。（牛津）

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: must侧重于说活者的主观看法，认为有必要或有义务去做某事。
have to侧重于客观需要，含有“不得不”或“被迫”之意。
